The paper deals with the problem of coded caching, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the allocation of memory and the optimization of delivery rate, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The structured clique cover algorithm is a graph-based approach, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and also has applications in social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves optimization and analytical characterization, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG).
